llm response:
Step 1: Determine how much money was made off the jerseys. It is 113 t-shirts x $ 25 = $ 2825.  
Step 2: Determine how much money was made off the t-shirts. It is 78 jerseys x $ 115 = $ 9005.  
Step 3: Determine how much money was made in total. It is 2825 + 9005 = $ 11,830.  
Step 4: Determine how much more a jersey costs than a t-shirt. It is 9005 - 2825 = $ 6180.
